    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-12">
            <h2 id="overview">Overview</h2>
            <p>The <strong>DailyPlan System</strong> is a comprehensive planning and task management feature enabling administrators to create and manage development plans for the Comserv application and specific modules (e.g., BMaster beekeeping operations).</p>
            
            <h3>Key Features</h3>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Plan Management</strong>: Create, edit, delete, and organize plans by project</li>
                <li><strong>Task Linking</strong>: Associate todos with plans for tracking work items</li>
                <li><strong>Task Dependencies</strong>: Block tasks and prevent circular dependencies</li>
                <li><strong>Project Integration</strong>: Link plans to projects for organizational context</li>
                <li><strong>Admin-Only Access</strong>: Restricted to CSC admins and SiteName admins</li>
                <li><strong>Code Reuse</strong>: Leverages existing Todo, Project, and Calendar systems</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-12">
            <h2 id="architecture">Architecture Overview</h2>
            
            <h3>Database Schema</h3>
            <p><strong>New Tables:</strong></p>
            <ul>
                <li><code>dailyplan</code>: Aggregator table storing plan metadata</li>
                <li><code>dailyplan_project</code>: Link table (many-to-many) connecting plans to projects</li>
            </ul>
            
            <p><strong>Extended Tables:</strong></p>
            <ul>
                <li><code>todo</code>: Add <code>plan_id</code> (foreign key to dailyplan) and <code>blocked_by_todo_id</code> (self-reference for dependencies)</li>
            </ul>
            
            <h3>Permission Model</h3>
            <table class="table table-bordered">
                <thead>
                    <tr>
                        <th>Role</th>
                        <th>Access Level</th>
                    </tr>
                </thead>
                <tbody>
                    <tr>
                        <td>CSC Admin</td>
                        <td>All plans, all sites</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>SiteName Admin</td>
                        <td>Plans for their site only</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>Developer</td>
                        <td>No access</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>User</td>
                        <td>No access</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>Not Logged In</td>
                        <td>No access</td>
                    </tr>
                </tbody>
            </table>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-12">
            <h2 id="hierarchy">Project Hierarchy</h2>
            <p>The DailyPlan system sits within a larger project hierarchy to ensure proper organization and reporting:</p>
            <div style="background: #f0f4f7; padding: 20px; border-radius: 8px; border: 1px solid #d0d7de;">
                <ul style="list-style-type: none; padding-left: 0;">
                    <li style="font-weight: bold; margin-bottom: 10px;">📂 Project Management (Primary Parent)</li>
                    <li style="margin-left: 20px; margin-bottom: 10px;">└─ 📂 DailyPlan System (Sub-project)</li>
                    <li style="margin-left: 40px; color: #57606a;">└─ 📂 Daily Priorities (Active execution sub-project)</li>
                </ul>
                <p style="margin-top: 15px; font-size: 0.9em;"><strong>Purpose of "Daily Priorities":</strong> This sub-project is the specific container for tasks generated daily. It allows for high-granularity tracking of daily work without cluttering the main DailyPlan system metadata.</p>
            </div>

            <h2 id="phases">Implementation Phases</h2>
            
            <div class="phase-container">
                <h3 id="phase-1">Phase 1: Database Schema & Models (2-3 hours)</h3>
                <p><strong>Status:</strong> ⏳ PENDING</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>1. Create Result Files First (Required - blocking other tasks)</strong>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Create <code>Comserv/lib/Comserv/Model/Schema/Ency/Result/DailyPlan.pm</code> - Aggregator table definition</li>
                            <li>Create <code>Comserv/lib/Comserv/Model/Schema/Ency/Result/DailyPlanProject.pm</code> - Link table (many-to-many)</li>
                            <li>Update <code>Comserv/lib/Comserv/Model/Schema/Ency/Result/Todo.pm</code> - Add <code>plan_id</code> and <code>blocked_by_todo_id</code> relationships</li>
                        </ul>
                        <div style="background: #f5f9ff; border-left: 3px solid var(--secondary-color); padding: 12px; margin: 12px 0; border-radius: 3px;">
                            <p style="margin: 0 0 10px 0; font-size: 0.95em;"><strong>📚 Resources for Creating Result Files:</strong></p>
                            <ul style="margin: 8px 0; padding-left: 20px;">
                                <li><a href="/Documentation/Result_Class_Development_Guide" style="color: var(--secondary-color); text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 1px dashed var(--secondary-color);">Result_Class_Development_Guide.tt</a> - Step-by-step guide for creating DBIC Result classes</li>
                                <li><a href="/Documentation/DBIDocument" style="color: var(--secondary-color); text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 1px dashed var(--secondary-color);">DBIDocument.tt</a> - DBIx::Class ORM reference and patterns</li>
                                <li><a href="/Documentation/models/Todo" style="color: var(--secondary-color); text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 1px dashed var(--secondary-color);">models/Todo.tt</a> - Existing Todo model example (study this as reference)</li>
                                <li><a href="/Documentation/Schema" style="color: var(--secondary-color); text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 1px dashed var(--secondary-color);">Schema.tt</a> - Database schema overview and naming conventions</li>
                                <li><a href="/Documentation/AI_Chat_Schema_Documentation" style="color: var(--secondary-color); text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 1px dashed var(--secondary-color);">AI_Chat_Schema_Documentation.tt</a> - Advanced schema patterns and relationship examples</li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>
                    </li>
                    <li>2. Create tables via browser-based schema system (Comserv Admin > Database > Schema Designer)
                        <div style="background: #f5f9ff; border-left: 3px solid var(--secondary-color); padding: 12px; margin: 12px 0; border-radius: 3px;">
                            <p style="margin: 0 0 10px 0; font-size: 0.95em;"><strong>📚 Resources for Schema Management:</strong></p>
                            <ul style="margin: 8px 0; padding-left: 20px;">
                                <li><a href="/Documentation/DBSchemaManager_Usage_Guide" style="color: var(--secondary-color); text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 1px dashed var(--secondary-color);">DBSchemaManager_Usage_Guide.tt</a> - How to use the schema management browser tools</li>
                                <li><a href="/Documentation/controllers/Todo" style="color: var(--secondary-color); text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 1px dashed var(--secondary-color);">controllers/Todo.tt</a> - Todo controller example showing Result class usage</li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>
                    </li>
                    <li>3. Verify schema relationships in database</li>
                </ul>
                <p style="background: #fff3cd; border: 1px solid #ffc107; padding: 10px; border-radius: 4px; margin-top: 10px;"><strong>⚠️ Blocker:</strong> API token/key system not yet configured for programmatic database access. Tasks will be managed via browser interface until API endpoints are available.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="phase-container">
                <h3>Phase 2: Controller & Business Logic (3-4 hours)</h3>
                <p><strong>Status:</strong> ⏳ PENDING</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Create DailyPlan.pm controller with admin-only authorization</li>
                    <li>Implement plan CRUD actions (index, view, create, edit, delete)</li>
                    <li>Implement plan-todo linking (add_todo_to_plan, remove_todo_from_plan)</li>
                    <li>Reuse existing Todo controller for task management</li>
                    <li>Add business logic layer (get_plans_for_user, create_plan, etc.)</li>
                    <li>Add unit tests for controller and model</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="phase-container">
                <h3>Phase 3: Views & Frontend (3-4 hours)</h3>
                <p><strong>Status:</strong> ⏳ PENDING</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Analyze and extend existing <code>/admin/documentation/DailyPlan.tt</code></li>
                    <li>Add admin-only "Plan Management" tab</li>
                    <li>Create plan list view with filtering and sorting</li>
                    <li>Integrate existing Calendar component</li>
                    <li>Create plan detail view with todos and blocking status</li>
                    <li>Reuse existing components (todo items, project selector, calendar)</li>
                    <li>Apply theme integration and responsive design</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="phase-container">
                <h3>Phase 4: Integration & Testing (2 hours)</h3>
                <p><strong>Status:</strong> ⏳ PENDING</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Test Todo system integration (plan_id associations, cascading deletes)</li>
                    <li>Test Project associations (many-to-many linking)</li>
                    <li>Update navigation menu (add DailyPlan link)</li>
                    <li>Verify backward compatibility with existing DailyPlan.tt documentation</li>
                    <li>Run full test suite</li>
                    <li>Manual verification checklist (create plans, link todos, test permissions)</li>
                    <li>Cross-browser and responsive testing</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="phase-container">
                <h3>Phase 5: Documentation & Closure (1-2 hours)</h3>
                <p><strong>Status:</strong> ⏳ PENDING</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Update existing documentation in DailyPlan.tt with planning sections</li>
                    <li>Create/update API documentation for DailyPlan endpoints</li>
                    <li>Create database schema documentation</li>
                    <li>Create implementation report</li>
                    <li>Final code review and cleanup</li>
                    <li>Verify backward compatibility</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-12">
            <h2 id="decisions">Key Architectural Decisions</h2>
            <ol>
                <li><strong>✅ Todo/Task Unification</strong>: Extend existing <code>todo</code> table instead of creating separate <code>DailyPlanTask</code> table</li>
                <li><strong>✅ Project Relationship</strong>: Plans link to Projects via <code>dailyplan_project</code> link table</li>
                <li><strong>✅ Admin-Only Access</strong>: Restricted to CSC and SiteName admins</li>
                <li><strong>✅ Task Dependencies</strong>: Add <code>blocked_by_todo_id</code> for blocking relationships</li>
                <li><strong>✅ Calendar Integration</strong>: Reuse existing Todo Calendar component</li>
                <li><strong>✅ View Repurposing</strong>: Extend <code>/admin/documentation/DailyPlan.tt</code> instead of creating new templates</li>
                <li><strong>✅ Code Reuse Philosophy</strong>: Leverage existing Todo, Project, Calendar, Authorization systems</li>
            </ol>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-12">
            <h2 id="workflow">Admin Workflow</h2>
            
            <div class="phase-container">
                <h3>1. Create a Plan</h3>
                <p>Navigate to Admin > DailyPlan > Create Plan</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Name the plan (e.g., "Q1 2026 Development")</li>
                    <li>Set date range (plan_date_start, plan_date_end)</li>
                    <li>Select associated project(s)</li>
                    <li>Set priority and visibility</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="phase-container">
                <h3>2. Add Todos to Plan</h3>
                <p>Link existing todos to the plan</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Select plan</li>
                    <li>Browse available todos</li>
                    <li>Assign to plan (sets plan_id on todo)</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="phase-container">
                <h3>3. Manage Dependencies</h3>
                <p>Block todos based on other tasks</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Set <code>blocked_by_todo_id</code> on dependent tasks</li>
                    <li>System prevents circular blocking</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="phase-container">
                <h3>4. Track Progress</h3>
                <p>View plan status</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>See all todos in the plan</li>
                    <li>Identify blocked tasks</li>
                    <li>Update todo status from plan view</li>
                    <li>See project context</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-12">
